          <td valign="top">

<span class="txth1">Advancer Abbreviation : create code snippet through vim abbreviation</span> 

<br>
<br>

<!-- karma table -->
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="1" bordercolor="#000066">
<tr>
  <td class="lightbg"><b>&nbsp;script karma&nbsp;</b></td>
  <td>
    Rating <b>0/0</b>,
    Downloaded by 29  </td>
  <td class="lightbg">
  <b>&nbsp;Comments, bugs, improvements&nbsp;</b>
  </td>
  <td>
    <a href="http://vim.wikia.com/wiki/Script:3598">Vim wiki</a>
  </td>  
</tr>
</table>
<p>

<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
<tr><td class="prompt">created by</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=17938">Miao Jiang</a></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">script type</td></tr>
<tr><td>utility</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">description</td></tr>
<tr><td>Repository, Tutorial: <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/jiangmiao/advancer-abbreviation">https://github.com/jiangmiao/advancer-abbreviation</A><br><br>Advancer Abbreviation<br>=====================<br>Advancer Abbreviation is a Vim plugin to create code snippet quickly<br><br>Usage<br>-----<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use Shortcut &lt;C-CR&gt; or &lt;S-CR&gt; to expand the abbreviation or jump to next placeholder.<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;S-CR&gt; : Smart Expand or jump to next placeholder.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;C-CR&gt; : Force Expand or jump to next placeholder.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;ESC&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;: If the line contain placeholder but now it is blank, <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; then delete whole line and leave insert mode.<br><br>Features<br>--------<br>*&nbsp;&nbsp; Support any character except space as abbreviate name.<br>*&nbsp;&nbsp; Quick jump to next placeholder.<br>*&nbsp;&nbsp; Easy to extend.<br><br>Installation<br>------------<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;copy plugin/advancer-abbreviate.vim to ~/.vim/plugin<br><br>Tutorial<br>--------<br>###Preparation<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;copy ftplugin-examples/* to ~/.vim/ftplugin<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;There are 5 examples include c, cpp, javascript, php, ruby<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The abbreviation supported in example are<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;c&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;: for std main #i #ii<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;cpp&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;: for std main<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;javascript : for fu<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ruby&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : for def<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;php&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;: for<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You could test the script with your favourite language.<br><br>###example for edit C file<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;C-CR&gt; = Control+Return<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;= Cursor postion<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$ gvim foo.c<br><br>1<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;input: #i&lt;C-CR&gt;foo&lt;C-CR&gt;#ii&lt;C-CR&gt;bar&lt;C-CR&gt;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;output:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#include &lt;foo&gt;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#include &quot;bar&quot;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;|<br><br>2<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;input: std&lt;C-CR&gt;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;output:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#include &lt;stdlib.h&gt;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#include &lt;string.h&gt;<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;|<br><br>Write Your Own Abbreviation<br>---------------------------<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use Command Abbr<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usage: Abbr [name] [code]<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Example:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Abbr for for (/*TODO*/; /*TODO*/; /*TODO*/) {&lt;CR&gt;/*TODO*/&lt;CR&gt;}&lt;CR&gt;/*TODO*/<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Abbr #ii #include &quot;/*TODO*/&quot;&lt;CR&gt;<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Abbreviate format is same as vim abbr. see help :abbr<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;but AdvAbbr has looser limition on name, it support any character as name except space.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;eg: f.f is invalid name in vim abbr but valid in Advancer Abbreviation.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TODO has four different formats<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/*TODO*/, #TODO#, 'TODO', &lt;!--TODO--&gt;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;choose them according to which language is using. <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;for example, /*TODO*/ use for c, cpp, 'TODO' use for ruby<br></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">install details</td></tr>
<tr><td>copy plugin/advancer-abbreviate.vim to ~/.vim/plugin</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
</table>

